name: GenieWords
author: GenieWords

sections.description:
GenieWords is a platform where you can easily and effortlessly market your business. We work with small businesses who don’t have budgets higher than USD 600.
This plugin will help you easily integrate your WooCommerce webshop with Facebook catalogue and Google Merchant center.
It will keep your products updated in both Google Merchant center and the Facebook catalogue.
Behind the scenes there is a process running in the background, keeping your products synchronized every 6 hour.

GenieWords account

To be able to use this plugin you need to sign up for an account at https://app.geniewords.com/register. After you’ve done this you can access the plugin and sign in with your GenieWords account.
In the plugin, this section is purely for connecting your GenieWords account.

Google Shopping

This is one of the products we have available for you to market your products through. The tab in the plugin contains 3 options. You can choose whether you want to use products variants or not. You can choose whether you want to use the long or short descriptions for your products, when your market them on Google. Last but not least you have a synchronize button, by pressing this button it will synchronize your products to your Google Merchant center which you have connected in your GenieWords account.
We will try to claim your URL, however if we can’t then we will tell you about this for you to be able to claim it yourself.

Facebook

The last tab in the plugin opens up for you being able to synchronize your products to your Facebook catalogue. If you don’t have a catalogue the plugin will generate a new catalogue for you which it will use to keep your products up to date.
It will also make sure to insert your Facebook pixel which you have also connected to your GenieWords account.
sections.installation:
1. Upload the plugin files to the /wp-content/plugins/’ directory, or install the plugin through the WordPress plugins screen directly.
  2. Activate the plugin through the /Plugins/ screen in WordPress
  3. Connect with your GenieWords account
  4. Click on Sync to connect on respective tabs
